# Next.js SOP

- App Router (`app/`) for new routes; Server Components default; `"use client"` only when needed.
- Colocate `loading.tsx` / `error.tsx` for route UX boundaries.
- Env: `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` for browser; secrets server-only.

## SSR / 缓存 / CWV

- Prefer static/ISR where data allows; document revalidate seconds in code comment.
- `fetch` cache options explicit (`force-cache`, `no-store`, `revalidate`) — no accidental stale UI.
- Dynamic routes: streaming + Suspense for slow segments; avoid blocking entire page.
- Images: `next/image` with sizes; fonts via `next/font` to reduce layout shift (CWV).
- Monitor LCP/CLS/INP in staging; lazy-load below-fold client components.
- API routes colocated in `app/api/`; validate input; map errors to stable JSON.

## Auth / Supabase（若项目使用）

- Server 侧用 `getUser()` / 校验 session，**勿**仅用 `getSession()` 作授权依据（易伪造 cookie）
- RLS 默认开启；Service role key **仅** server ·  never `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`
- Stripe/支付密钥：server-only env；webhook 验签
- Middleware：保护路由与 redirect 逻辑与 RLS 一致

## 验证

- `npm run lint` · `type-check` · `test` · `build` before marking tasks done.
- E2E optional Playwright when project has config.
